1. Definitions
--------------

1.1. "Contributor"
    means each individual or legal entity that creates, contributes to
    the creation of, or owns Covered Software.

1.2. "Contributor's Copyright"
    means the copyright in the Contributor's portion of Covered Software.

1.3. "Covered Software"
    means Source Code Form to which the initial Contributor has attached the
    notice in Exhibit A, the Executable Form of such Source Code Form, and
    Modifications of and/or to Covered Software.

1.4. "Executable Form"
    means any form other than Source Code Form.

1.5. "Initial Developer"
    means the individual or legal entity that first creates Covered Software
    and makes that Covered Software available under this License.

1.6. "Larger Work"
    means a work that combines Covered Software with other material,
    developed by a particular Contributor, in a way that causes the
    contribution's Covered Software to be in Source Code Form, but the
    combination as a whole is not Covered Software.

1.7. "License"
    means this document.

1.8. "Licensable"
    means having the right to grant, to the maximum extent possible, whether
    at the time of the initial grant or subsequently, any and all of the
    rights conveyed by this License.

1.9. "Modifications"
    means any of the following:

    a. any addition to or deletion from the substance or structure of
       Covered Software;

    b. any new Source Code Form or compilation of Source Code Form that
       is derived from or is based on Covered Software; or

    c. any new Executable Form that is derived from or is based on
       Covered Software.

1.10. "Source Code Form"
    means the form in which a program's source code is presented for
    human modification.

1.11. "You"
    (or "Your") means an individual or a legal entity exercising rights
    under this License. For legal entities, "You" includes any entity that
    controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with You. For
    purposes of this definition, "control" means (a) the power, direct or
    indirect, to cause the direction or management of such entity, whether
    by contract or otherwise, or (b) ownership of fifty percent (50%) or
    more of the outstanding shares or beneficial ownership of such entity.

